Kenya's Abraham Kiptum is the new World half Marathon record holder. The Daegu Marathon champion on Sunday shattered the long-standing record held by Eritrean Zersenay Tadese after clocking 58:19 to win the Valencia half Marathon on Sunday. Kiptum shaved off four seconds from the previous record set by Tadese in Lisbon in 2010. ...MORE TO FOLLOW...   Mo Farah lift men's title with a personal best No one claims responsibility as journalist is shot dead in Mogadishu